1667Constant *GetConstantFoldFPValue(double V, Type *Ty) {
1668 if (Ty->isHalfTy() || Ty->isFloatTy()) {
1669 APFloat APF(V);
1670 bool unused;
1671 APF.convert(Ty->getFltSemantics(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &unused);
1672 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), APF);
1673 }
1674 if (Ty->isDoubleTy())
1675 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), APFloat(V));
1676 llvm_unreachable("Can only constant fold half/float/double");
1677}
1678
1679/// Clear the floating-point exception state.
1680inline void llvm_fenv_clearexcept() {
1681#if defined(HAVE_FENV_H) && HAVE_DECL_FE_ALL_EXCEPT
1682 feclearexcept(FE_ALL_EXCEPT);
1683#endif
1684 errno = 0;
1685}
1686
1687/// Test if a floating-point exception was raised.
1688inline bool llvm_fenv_testexcept() {
1689 int errno_val = errno;
1690 if (errno_val == ERANGE || errno_val == EDOM)
1691 return true;
1692#if defined(HAVE_FENV_H) && HAVE_DECL_FE_ALL_EXCEPT && HAVE_DECL_FE_INEXACT
1693 if (fetestexcept(FE_ALL_EXCEPT & ~FE_INEXACT))
1694 return true;
1695#endif
1696 return false;
1697}
1698
1699Constant *ConstantFoldFP(double (*NativeFP)(double), double V, Type *Ty) {
1700 llvm_fenv_clearexcept();
1701 V = NativeFP(V);
1702 if (llvm_fenv_testexcept()) {
1703 llvm_fenv_clearexcept();
1704 return nullptr;
1705 }
1706
1707 return GetConstantFoldFPValue(V, Ty);
1708}
1709
1710Constant *ConstantFoldBinaryFP(double (*NativeFP)(double, double), double V,
1711 double W, Type *Ty) {
1712 llvm_fenv_clearexcept();
1713 V = NativeFP(V, W);
1714 if (llvm_fenv_testexcept()) {
1715 llvm_fenv_clearexcept();
1716 return nullptr;
1717 }
1718
1719 return GetConstantFoldFPValue(V, Ty);
1720}
1721
1722Constant *ConstantFoldVectorReduce(Intrinsic::ID IID, Constant *Op) {
1723 FixedVectorType *VT = dyn_cast<FixedVectorType>(Op->getType());
1724 if (!VT)
1725 return nullptr;
1726 ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Op->getAggregateElement(0U));
1727 if (!CI)
1728 return nullptr;
1729 APInt Acc = CI->getValue();
1730
1731 for (unsigned I = 1; I < VT->getNumElements(); I++) {
1732 if (!(CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Op->getAggregateElement(I))))
1733 return nullptr;
1734 const APInt &X = CI->getValue();
1735 switch (IID) {
1736 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_add:
1737 Acc = Acc + X;
1738 break;
1739 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_mul:
1740 Acc = Acc * X;
1741 break;
1742 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_and:
1743 Acc = Acc & X;
1744 break;
1745 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_or:
1746 Acc = Acc | X;
1747 break;
1748 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_xor:
1749 Acc = Acc ^ X;
1750 break;
1751 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_smin:
1752 Acc = APIntOps::smin(Acc, X);
1753 break;
1754 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_smax:
1755 Acc = APIntOps::smax(Acc, X);
1756 break;
1757 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_umin:
1758 Acc = APIntOps::umin(Acc, X);
1759 break;
1760 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_umax:
1761 Acc = APIntOps::umax(Acc, X);
1762 break;
1763 }
1764 }
1765
1766 return ConstantInt::get(Op->getContext(), Acc);
1767}
1768
1769/// Attempt to fold an SSE floating point to integer conversion of a constant
1770/// floating point. If roundTowardZero is false, the default IEEE rounding is
1771/// used (toward nearest, ties to even). This matches the behavior of the
1772/// non-truncating SSE instructions in the default rounding mode. The desired
1773/// integer type Ty is used to select how many bits are available for the
1774/// result. Returns null if the conversion cannot be performed, otherwise
1775/// returns the Constant value resulting from the conversion.
1776Constant *ConstantFoldSSEConvertToInt(const APFloat &Val, bool roundTowardZero,
1777 Type *Ty, bool IsSigned) {
1778 // All of these conversion intrinsics form an integer of at most 64bits.
1779 unsigned ResultWidth = Ty->getIntegerBitWidth();
1780 assert(ResultWidth <= 64 &&
1781 "Can only constant fold conversions to 64 and 32 bit ints");
1782
1783 uint64_t UIntVal;
1784 bool isExact = false;
1785 APFloat::roundingMode mode = roundTowardZero? APFloat::rmTowardZero
1786 : APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven;
1787 APFloat::opStatus status =
1788 Val.convertToInteger(makeMutableArrayRef(UIntVal), ResultWidth,
1789 IsSigned, mode, &isExact);
1790 if (status != APFloat::opOK &&
1791 (!roundTowardZero || status != APFloat::opInexact))
1792 return nullptr;
1793 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, UIntVal, IsSigned);
1794}
1795
1796double getValueAsDouble(ConstantFP *Op) {
1797 Type *Ty = Op->getType();
1798
1799 if (Ty->isFloatTy())
1800 return Op->getValueAPF().convertToFloat();
1801
1802 if (Ty->isDoubleTy())
1803 return Op->getValueAPF().convertToDouble();
1804
1805 bool unused;
1806 APFloat APF = Op->getValueAPF();
1807 APF.convert(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &unused);
1808 return APF.convertToDouble();
1809}
1810
1811static bool isManifestConstant(const Constant *c) {
1812 if (isa<ConstantData>(c)) {
1813 return true;
1814 } else if (isa<ConstantAggregate>(c) || isa<ConstantExpr>(c)) {
1815 for (const Value *subc : c->operand_values()) {
1816 if (!isManifestConstant(cast<Constant>(subc)))
1817 return false;
1818 }
1819 return true;
1820 }
1821 return false;
1822}
1823
1824static bool getConstIntOrUndef(Value *Op, const APInt *&C) {
1825 if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Op)) {
1826 C = &CI->getValue();
1827 return true;
1828 }
1829 if (isa<UndefValue>(Op)) {
1830 C = nullptr;
1831 return true;
1832 }
1833 return false;
1834}
1835
1836static Constant *ConstantFoldScalarCall1(StringRef Name,
1837 Intrinsic::ID IntrinsicID,
1838 Type *Ty,
1839 ArrayRef<Constant *> Operands,
1840 const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI,
1841 const CallBase *Call) {
1842 assert(Operands.size() == 1 && "Wrong number of operands.");
1843
1844 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::is_constant) {
1845 // We know we have a "Constant" argument. But we want to only
1846 // return true for manifest constants, not those that depend on
1847 // constants with unknowable values, e.g. GlobalValue or BlockAddress.
1848 if (isManifestConstant(Operands[0]))
1849 return ConstantInt::getTrue(Ty->getContext());
1850 return nullptr;
1851 }
1852 if (isa<UndefValue>(Operands[0])) {
1853 // cosine(arg) is between -1 and 1. cosine(invalid arg) is NaN.
1854 // ctpop() is between 0 and bitwidth, pick 0 for undef.
1855 // fptoui.sat and fptosi.sat can always fold to zero (for a zero input).
1856 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::cos ||
1857 IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::ctpop ||
1858 IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::fptoui_sat ||
1859 IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::fptosi_sat)
1860 return Constant::getNullValue(Ty);
1861 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::bswap ||
1862 IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::bitreverse ||
1863 IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::launder_invariant_group ||
1864 IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::strip_invariant_group)
1865 return Operands[0];
1866 }
1867
1868 if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(Operands[0])) {
1869 // launder(null) == null == strip(null) iff in addrspace 0
1870 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::launder_invariant_group ||
1871 IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::strip_invariant_group) {
1872 // If instruction is not yet put in a basic block (e.g. when cloning
1873 // a function during inlining), Call's caller may not be available.
1874 // So check Call's BB first before querying Call->getCaller.
1875 const Function *Caller =
1876 Call->getParent() ? Call->getCaller() : nullptr;
1877 if (Caller &&
1878 !NullPointerIsDefined(
1879 Caller, Operands[0]->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace())) {
1880 return Operands[0];
1881 }
1882 return nullptr;
1883 }
1884 }
1885
1886 if (auto *Op = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Operands[0])) {
1887 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::convert_to_fp16) {
1888 APFloat Val(Op->getValueAPF());
1889
1890 bool lost = false;
1891 Val.convert(APFloat::IEEEhalf(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &lost);
1892
1893 return ConstantInt::get(Ty->getContext(), Val.bitcastToAPInt());
1894 }
1895
1896 APFloat U = Op->getValueAPF();
1897
1898 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::wasm_trunc_signed ||
1899 IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::wasm_trunc_unsigned ||
1900 IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::wasm_trunc_saturate_signed ||
1901 IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::wasm_trunc_saturate_unsigned) {
1902
1903 bool Saturating = IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::wasm_trunc_saturate_signed ||
1904 IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::wasm_trunc_saturate_unsigned;
1905 bool Signed = IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::wasm_trunc_signed ||
1906 IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::wasm_trunc_saturate_signed;
1907
1908 if (U.isNaN())
1909 return Saturating ? ConstantInt::get(Ty, 0) : nullptr;
1910
1911 unsigned Width = Ty->getIntegerBitWidth();
1912 APSInt Int(Width, !Signed);
1913 bool IsExact = false;
1914 APFloat::opStatus Status =
1915 U.convertToInteger(Int, APFloat::rmTowardZero, &IsExact);
1916
1917 if (Status == APFloat::opOK || Status == APFloat::opInexact)
1918 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, Int);
1919
1920 if (!Saturating)
1921 return nullptr;
1922
1923 if (U.isNegative())
1924 return Signed ? ConstantInt::get(Ty, APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width))
1925 : ConstantInt::get(Ty, APInt::getMinValue(Width));
1926 else
1927 return Signed ? ConstantInt::get(Ty, APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width))
1928 : ConstantInt::get(Ty, APInt::getMaxValue(Width));
1929 }
1930
1931 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::fptoui_sat ||
1932 IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::fptosi_sat) {
1933 // convertToInteger() already has the desired saturation semantics.
1934 APSInt Int(Ty->getIntegerBitWidth(),
1935 IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::fptoui_sat);
1936 bool IsExact;
1937 U.convertToInteger(Int, APFloat::rmTowardZero, &IsExact);
1938 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, Int);
1939 }
1940
1941 if (!Ty->isHalfTy() && !Ty->isFloatTy() && !Ty->isDoubleTy())
1942 return nullptr;
1943
1944 // Use internal versions of these intrinsics.
1945
1946 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::nearbyint || IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::rint) {
1947 U.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
1948 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), U);
1949 }
1950
1951 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::round) {
1952 U.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmNearestTiesToAway);
1953 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), U);
1954 }
1955
1956 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::roundeven) {
1957 U.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
1958 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), U);
1959 }
1960
1961 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::ceil) {
1962 U.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmTowardPositive);
1963 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), U);
1964 }
1965
1966 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::floor) {
1967 U.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmTowardNegative);
1968 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), U);
1969 }
1970
1971 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::trunc) {
1972 U.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmTowardZero);
1973 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), U);
1974 }
1975
1976 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::fabs) {
1977 U.clearSign();
1978 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), U);
1979 }
1980
1981 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_fract) {
1982 // The v_fract instruction behaves like the OpenCL spec, which defines
1983 // fract(x) as fmin(x - floor(x), 0x1.fffffep-1f): "The min() operator is
1984 // there to prevent fract(-small) from returning 1.0. It returns the
1985 // largest positive floating-point number less than 1.0."
1986 APFloat FloorU(U);
1987 FloorU.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmTowardNegative);
1988 APFloat FractU(U - FloorU);
1989 APFloat AlmostOne(U.getSemantics(), 1);
1990 AlmostOne.next(/*nextDown*/ true);
1991 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), minimum(FractU, AlmostOne));
1992 }
1993
1994 // Rounding operations (floor, trunc, ceil, round and nearbyint) do not
1995 // raise FP exceptions, unless the argument is signaling NaN.
1996
1997 Optional<APFloat::roundingMode> RM;
1998 switch (IntrinsicID) {
1999 default:
2000 break;
2001 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_nearbyint:
2002 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_rint: {
2003 auto CI = cast<ConstrainedFPIntrinsic>(Call);
2004 RM = CI->getRoundingMode();
2005 if (!RM || RM.getValue() == RoundingMode::Dynamic)
2006 return nullptr;
2007 break;
2008 }
2009 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_round:
2010 RM = APFloat::rmNearestTiesToAway;
2011 break;
2012 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_ceil:
2013 RM = APFloat::rmTowardPositive;
2014 break;
2015 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_floor:
2016 RM = APFloat::rmTowardNegative;
2017 break;
2018 case Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_trunc:
2019 RM = APFloat::rmTowardZero;
2020 break;
2021 }
2022 if (RM) {
2023 auto CI = cast<ConstrainedFPIntrinsic>(Call);
2024 if (U.isFinite()) {
2025 APFloat::opStatus St = U.roundToIntegral(*RM);
2026 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::experimental_constrained_rint &&
2027 St == APFloat::opInexact) {
2028 Optional<fp::ExceptionBehavior> EB = CI->getExceptionBehavior();
2029 if (EB && *EB == fp::ebStrict)
2030 return nullptr;
2031 }
2032 } else if (U.isSignaling()) {
2033 Optional<fp::ExceptionBehavior> EB = CI->getExceptionBehavior();
2034 if (EB && *EB != fp::ebIgnore)
2035 return nullptr;
2036 U = APFloat::getQNaN(U.getSemantics());
2037 }
2038 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), U);
2039 }
2040
2041 /// We only fold functions with finite arguments. Folding NaN and inf is
2042 /// likely to be aborted with an exception anyway, and some host libms
2043 /// have known errors raising exceptions.
2044 if (!U.isFinite())
2045 return nullptr;
2046
2047 /// Currently APFloat versions of these functions do not exist, so we use
2048 /// the host native double versions. Float versions are not called
2049 /// directly but for all these it is true (float)(f((double)arg)) ==
2050 /// f(arg). Long double not supported yet.
2051 double V = getValueAsDouble(Op);
2052
2053 switch (IntrinsicID) {
2054 default: break;
2055 case Intrinsic::log:
2056 return ConstantFoldFP(log, V, Ty);
2057 case Intrinsic::log2:
2058 // TODO: What about hosts that lack a C99 library?
2059 return ConstantFoldFP(Log2, V, Ty);
2060 case Intrinsic::log10:
2061 // TODO: What about hosts that lack a C99 library?
2062 return ConstantFoldFP(log10, V, Ty);
2063 case Intrinsic::exp:
2064 return ConstantFoldFP(exp, V, Ty);
2065 case Intrinsic::exp2:
2066 // Fold exp2(x) as pow(2, x), in case the host lacks a C99 library.
2067 return ConstantFoldBinaryFP(pow, 2.0, V, Ty);
2068 case Intrinsic::sin:
2069 return ConstantFoldFP(sin, V, Ty);
2070 case Intrinsic::cos:
2071 return ConstantFoldFP(cos, V, Ty);
2072 case Intrinsic::sqrt:
2073 return ConstantFoldFP(sqrt, V, Ty);
2074 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cos:
2075 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_sin:
2076 if (V < -256.0 || V > 256.0)
2077 // The gfx8 and gfx9 architectures handle arguments outside the range
2078 // [-256, 256] differently. This should be a rare case so bail out
2079 // rather than trying to handle the difference.
2080 return nullptr;
2081 bool IsCos = IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_cos;
2082 double V4 = V * 4.0;
2083 if (V4 == floor(V4)) {
2084 // Force exact results for quarter-integer inputs.
2085 const double SinVals[4] = { 0.0, 1.0, 0.0, -1.0 };
2086 V = SinVals[((int)V4 + (IsCos ? 1 : 0)) & 3];
2087 } else {
2088 if (IsCos)
2089 V = cos(V * 2.0 * numbers::pi);
2090 else
2091 V = sin(V * 2.0 * numbers::pi);
2092 }
2093 return GetConstantFoldFPValue(V, Ty);
2094 }
2095
2096 if (!TLI)
2097 return nullptr;
2098
2099 LibFunc Func = NotLibFunc;
2100 TLI->getLibFunc(Name, Func);
2101 switch (Func) {
2102 default:
2103 break;
2104 case LibFunc_acos:
2105 case LibFunc_acosf:
2106 case LibFunc_acos_finite:
2107 case LibFunc_acosf_finite:
2108 if (TLI->has(Func))
2109 return ConstantFoldFP(acos, V, Ty);
2110 break;
2111 case LibFunc_asin:
2112 case LibFunc_asinf:
2113 case LibFunc_asin_finite:
2114 case LibFunc_asinf_finite:
2115 if (TLI->has(Func))
2116 return ConstantFoldFP(asin, V, Ty);
2117 break;
2118 case LibFunc_atan:
2119 case LibFunc_atanf:
2120 if (TLI->has(Func))
2121 return ConstantFoldFP(atan, V, Ty);
2122 break;
2123 case LibFunc_ceil:
2124 case LibFunc_ceilf:
2125 if (TLI->has(Func)) {
2126 U.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmTowardPositive);
2127 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), U);
2128 }
2129 break;
2130 case LibFunc_cos:
2131 case LibFunc_cosf:
2132 if (TLI->has(Func))
2133 return ConstantFoldFP(cos, V, Ty);
2134 break;
2135 case LibFunc_cosh:
2136 case LibFunc_coshf:
2137 case LibFunc_cosh_finite:
2138 case LibFunc_coshf_finite:
2139 if (TLI->has(Func))
2140 return ConstantFoldFP(cosh, V, Ty);
2141 break;
2142 case LibFunc_exp:
2143 case LibFunc_expf:
2144 case LibFunc_exp_finite:
2145 case LibFunc_expf_finite:
2146 if (TLI->has(Func))
2147 return ConstantFoldFP(exp, V, Ty);
2148 break;
2149 case LibFunc_exp2:
2150 case LibFunc_exp2f:
2151 case LibFunc_exp2_finite:
2152 case LibFunc_exp2f_finite:
2153 if (TLI->has(Func))
2154 // Fold exp2(x) as pow(2, x), in case the host lacks a C99 library.
2155 return ConstantFoldBinaryFP(pow, 2.0, V, Ty);
2156 break;
2157 case LibFunc_fabs:
2158 case LibFunc_fabsf:
2159 if (TLI->has(Func)) {
2160 U.clearSign();
2161 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), U);
2162 }
2163 break;
2164 case LibFunc_floor:
2165 case LibFunc_floorf:
2166 if (TLI->has(Func)) {
2167 U.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmTowardNegative);
2168 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), U);
2169 }
2170 break;
2171 case LibFunc_log:
2172 case LibFunc_logf:
2173 case LibFunc_log_finite:
2174 case LibFunc_logf_finite:
2175 if (V > 0.0 && TLI->has(Func))
2176 return ConstantFoldFP(log, V, Ty);
2177 break;
2178 case LibFunc_log2:
2179 case LibFunc_log2f:
2180 case LibFunc_log2_finite:
2181 case LibFunc_log2f_finite:
2182 if (V > 0.0 && TLI->has(Func))
2183 // TODO: What about hosts that lack a C99 library?
2184 return ConstantFoldFP(Log2, V, Ty);
2185 break;
2186 case LibFunc_log10:
2187 case LibFunc_log10f:
2188 case LibFunc_log10_finite:
2189 case LibFunc_log10f_finite:
2190 if (V > 0.0 && TLI->has(Func))
2191 // TODO: What about hosts that lack a C99 library?
2192 return ConstantFoldFP(log10, V, Ty);
2193 break;
2194 case LibFunc_nearbyint:
2195 case LibFunc_nearbyintf:
2196 case LibFunc_rint:
2197 case LibFunc_rintf:
2198 if (TLI->has(Func)) {
2199 U.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
2200 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), U);
2201 }
2202 break;
2203 case LibFunc_round:
2204 case LibFunc_roundf:
2205 if (TLI->has(Func)) {
2206 U.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmNearestTiesToAway);
2207 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), U);
2208 }
2209 break;
2210 case LibFunc_sin:
2211 case LibFunc_sinf:
2212 if (TLI->has(Func))
2213 return ConstantFoldFP(sin, V, Ty);
2214 break;
2215 case LibFunc_sinh:
2216 case LibFunc_sinhf:
2217 case LibFunc_sinh_finite:
2218 case LibFunc_sinhf_finite:
2219 if (TLI->has(Func))
2220 return ConstantFoldFP(sinh, V, Ty);
2221 break;
2222 case LibFunc_sqrt:
2223 case LibFunc_sqrtf:
2224 if (V >= 0.0 && TLI->has(Func))
2225 return ConstantFoldFP(sqrt, V, Ty);
2226 break;
2227 case LibFunc_tan:
2228 case LibFunc_tanf:
2229 if (TLI->has(Func))
2230 return ConstantFoldFP(tan, V, Ty);
2231 break;
2232 case LibFunc_tanh:
2233 case LibFunc_tanhf:
2234 if (TLI->has(Func))
2235 return ConstantFoldFP(tanh, V, Ty);
2236 break;
2237 case LibFunc_trunc:
2238 case LibFunc_truncf:
2239 if (TLI->has(Func)) {
2240 U.roundToIntegral(APFloat::rmTowardZero);
2241 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), U);
2242 }
2243 break;
2244 }
2245 return nullptr;
2246 }
2247
2248 if (auto *Op = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Operands[0])) {
2249 switch (IntrinsicID) {
2250 case Intrinsic::bswap:
2251 return ConstantInt::get(Ty->getContext(), Op->getValue().byteSwap());
2252 case Intrinsic::ctpop:
2253 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, Op->getValue().countPopulation());
2254 case Intrinsic::bitreverse:
2255 return ConstantInt::get(Ty->getContext(), Op->getValue().reverseBits());
2256 case Intrinsic::convert_from_fp16: {
2257 APFloat Val(APFloat::IEEEhalf(), Op->getValue());
2258
2259 bool lost = false;
2260 APFloat::opStatus status = Val.convert(
2261 Ty->getFltSemantics(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven, &lost);
2262
2263 // Conversion is always precise.
2264 (void)status;
2265 assert(status == APFloat::opOK && !lost &&
2266 "Precision lost during fp16 constfolding");
2267
2268 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), Val);
2269 }
2270 default:
2271 return nullptr;
2272 }
2273 }
2274
2275 if (isa<ConstantAggregateZero>(Operands[0])) {
2276 switch (IntrinsicID) {
2277 default: break;
2278 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_add:
2279 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_mul:
2280 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_and:
2281 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_or:
2282 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_xor:
2283 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_smin:
2284 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_smax:
2285 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_umin:
2286 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_umax:
2287 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, 0);
2288 }
2289 }
2290
2291 // Support ConstantVector in case we have an Undef in the top.
2292 if (isa<ConstantVector>(Operands[0]) ||
2293 isa<ConstantDataVector>(Operands[0])) {
2294 auto *Op = cast<Constant>(Operands[0]);
2295 switch (IntrinsicID) {
2296 default: break;
2297 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_add:
2298 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_mul:
2299 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_and:
2300 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_or:
2301 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_xor:
2302 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_smin:
2303 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_smax:
2304 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_umin:
2305 case Intrinsic::vector_reduce_umax:
2306 if (Constant *C = ConstantFoldVectorReduce(IntrinsicID, Op))
2307 return C;
2308 break;
2309 case Intrinsic::x86_sse_cvtss2si:
2310 case Intrinsic::x86_sse_cvtss2si64:
2311 case Intrinsic::x86_sse2_cvtsd2si:
2312 case Intrinsic::x86_sse2_cvtsd2si64:
2313 if (ConstantFP *FPOp =
2314 dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantFP>(Op->getAggregateElement(0U)))
2315 return ConstantFoldSSEConvertToInt(FPOp->getValueAPF(),
2316 /*roundTowardZero=*/false, Ty,
2317 /*IsSigned*/true);
2318 break;
2319 case Intrinsic::x86_sse_cvttss2si:
2320 case Intrinsic::x86_sse_cvttss2si64:
2321 case Intrinsic::x86_sse2_cvttsd2si:
2322 case Intrinsic::x86_sse2_cvttsd2si64:
2323 if (ConstantFP *FPOp =
2324 dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantFP>(Op->getAggregateElement(0U)))
2325 return ConstantFoldSSEConvertToInt(FPOp->getValueAPF(),
2326 /*roundTowardZero=*/true, Ty,
2327 /*IsSigned*/true);
2328 break;
2329 }
2330 }
2331
2332 return nullptr;
2333}
2334
2335static Constant *ConstantFoldScalarCall2(StringRef Name,
2336 Intrinsic::ID IntrinsicID,
2337 Type *Ty,
2338 ArrayRef<Constant *> Operands,
2339 const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI,
2340 const CallBase *Call) {
2341 assert(Operands.size() == 2 && "Wrong number of operands.");
2342
2343 if (Ty->isFloatingPointTy()) {
2344 // TODO: We should have undef handling for all of the FP intrinsics that
2345 // are attempted to be folded in this function.
2346 bool IsOp0Undef = isa<UndefValue>(Operands[0]);
2347 bool IsOp1Undef = isa<UndefValue>(Operands[1]);
2348 switch (IntrinsicID) {
2349 case Intrinsic::maxnum:
2350 case Intrinsic::minnum:
2351 case Intrinsic::maximum:
2352 case Intrinsic::minimum:
2353 // If one argument is undef, return the other argument.
2354 if (IsOp0Undef)
2355 return Operands[1];
2356 if (IsOp1Undef)
2357 return Operands[0];
2358 break;
2359 }
2360 }
2361
2362 if (auto *Op1 = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Operands[0])) {
2363 if (!Ty->isHalfTy() && !Ty->isFloatTy() && !Ty->isDoubleTy())
2364 return nullptr;
2365 double Op1V = getValueAsDouble(Op1);
2366
2367 if (auto *Op2 = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Operands[1])) {
2368 if (Op2->getType() != Op1->getType())
2369 return nullptr;
2370
2371 double Op2V = getValueAsDouble(Op2);
2372 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::pow) {
2373 return ConstantFoldBinaryFP(pow, Op1V, Op2V, Ty);
2374 }
2375 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::copysign) {
2376 APFloat V1 = Op1->getValueAPF();
2377 const APFloat &V2 = Op2->getValueAPF();
2378 V1.copySign(V2);
2379 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), V1);
2380 }
2381
2382 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::minnum) {
2383 const APFloat &C1 = Op1->getValueAPF();
2384 const APFloat &C2 = Op2->getValueAPF();
2385 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), minnum(C1, C2));
2386 }
2387
2388 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::maxnum) {
2389 const APFloat &C1 = Op1->getValueAPF();
2390 const APFloat &C2 = Op2->getValueAPF();
2391 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), maxnum(C1, C2));
2392 }
2393
2394 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::minimum) {
2395 const APFloat &C1 = Op1->getValueAPF();
2396 const APFloat &C2 = Op2->getValueAPF();
2397 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), minimum(C1, C2));
2398 }
2399
2400 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::maximum) {
2401 const APFloat &C1 = Op1->getValueAPF();
2402 const APFloat &C2 = Op2->getValueAPF();
2403 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), maximum(C1, C2));
2404 }
2405
2406 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_fmul_legacy) {
2407 const APFloat &C1 = Op1->getValueAPF();
2408 const APFloat &C2 = Op2->getValueAPF();
2409 // The legacy behaviour is that multiplying +/- 0.0 by anything, even
2410 // NaN or infinity, gives +0.0.
2411 if (C1.isZero() || C2.isZero())
2412 return ConstantFP::getNullValue(Ty);
2413 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), C1 * C2);
2414 }
2415
2416 if (!TLI)
2417 return nullptr;
2418
2419 LibFunc Func = NotLibFunc;
2420 TLI->getLibFunc(Name, Func);
2421 switch (Func) {
2422 default:
2423 break;
2424 case LibFunc_pow:
2425 case LibFunc_powf:
2426 case LibFunc_pow_finite:
2427 case LibFunc_powf_finite:
2428 if (TLI->has(Func))
2429 return ConstantFoldBinaryFP(pow, Op1V, Op2V, Ty);
2430 break;
2431 case LibFunc_fmod:
2432 case LibFunc_fmodf:
2433 if (TLI->has(Func)) {
2434 APFloat V = Op1->getValueAPF();
2435 if (APFloat::opStatus::opOK == V.mod(Op2->getValueAPF()))
2436 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), V);
2437 }
2438 break;
2439 case LibFunc_remainder:
2440 case LibFunc_remainderf:
2441 if (TLI->has(Func)) {
2442 APFloat V = Op1->getValueAPF();
2443 if (APFloat::opStatus::opOK == V.remainder(Op2->getValueAPF()))
2444 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), V);
2445 }
2446 break;
2447 case LibFunc_atan2:
2448 case LibFunc_atan2f:
2449 case LibFunc_atan2_finite:
2450 case LibFunc_atan2f_finite:
2451 if (TLI->has(Func))
2452 return ConstantFoldBinaryFP(atan2, Op1V, Op2V, Ty);
2453 break;
2454 }
2455 } else if (auto *Op2C = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Operands[1])) {
2456 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::powi && Ty->isHalfTy())
2457 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(),
2458 APFloat((float)std::pow((float)Op1V,
2459 (int)Op2C->getZExtValue())));
2460 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::powi && Ty->isFloatTy())
2461 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(),
2462 APFloat((float)std::pow((float)Op1V,
2463 (int)Op2C->getZExtValue())));
2464 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::powi && Ty->isDoubleTy())
2465 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(),
2466 APFloat((double)std::pow((double)Op1V,
2467 (int)Op2C->getZExtValue())));
2468
2469 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::amdgcn_ldexp) {
2470 // FIXME: Should flush denorms depending on FP mode, but that's ignored
2471 // everywhere else.
2472
2473 // scalbn is equivalent to ldexp with float radix 2
2474 APFloat Result = scalbn(Op1->getValueAPF(), Op2C->getSExtValue(),
2475 APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
2476 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), Result);
2477 }
2478 }
2479 return nullptr;
2480 }
2481
2482 if (Operands[0]->getType()->isIntegerTy() &&
2483 Operands[1]->getType()->isIntegerTy()) {
2484 const APInt *C0, *C1;
2485 if (!getConstIntOrUndef(Operands[0], C0) ||
2486 !getConstIntOrUndef(Operands[1], C1))
2487 return nullptr;
2488
2489 unsigned BitWidth = Ty->getScalarSizeInBits();
2490 switch (IntrinsicID) {
2491 default: break;
2492 case Intrinsic::smax:
2493 if (!C0 && !C1)
2494 return UndefValue::get(Ty);
2495 if (!C0 || !C1)
2496 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, APInt::getSignedMaxValue(BitWidth));
2497 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, C0->sgt(*C1) ? *C0 : *C1);
2498
2499 case Intrinsic::smin:
2500 if (!C0 && !C1)
2501 return UndefValue::get(Ty);
2502 if (!C0 || !C1)
2503 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, APInt::getSignedMinValue(BitWidth));
2504 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, C0->slt(*C1) ? *C0 : *C1);
2505
2506 case Intrinsic::umax:
2507 if (!C0 && !C1)
2508 return UndefValue::get(Ty);
2509 if (!C0 || !C1)
2510 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, APInt::getMaxValue(BitWidth));
2511 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, C0->ugt(*C1) ? *C0 : *C1);
2512
2513 case Intrinsic::umin:
2514 if (!C0 && !C1)
2515 return UndefValue::get(Ty);
2516 if (!C0 || !C1)
2517 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, APInt::getMinValue(BitWidth));
2518 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, C0->ult(*C1) ? *C0 : *C1);
2519
2520 case Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow:
2521 case Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow:
2522 case Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow:
2523 case Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow:
2524 // X - undef -> { undef, false }
2525 // undef - X -> { undef, false }
2526 // X + undef -> { undef, false }
2527 // undef + x -> { undef, false }
2528 if (!C0 || !C1) {
2529 return ConstantStruct::get(
2530 cast<StructType>(Ty),
2531 {UndefValue::get(Ty->getStructElementType(0)),
2532 Constant::getNullValue(Ty->getStructElementType(1))});
2533 }
2534 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2535 case Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow:
2536 case Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow: {
2537 // undef * X -> { 0, false }
2538 // X * undef -> { 0, false }
2539 if (!C0 || !C1)
2540 return Constant::getNullValue(Ty);
2541
2542 APInt Res;
2543 bool Overflow;
2544 switch (IntrinsicID) {
2545 default: llvm_unreachable("Invalid case");
2546 case Intrinsic::sadd_with_overflow:
2547 Res = C0->sadd_ov(*C1, Overflow);
2548 break;
2549 case Intrinsic::uadd_with_overflow:
2550 Res = C0->uadd_ov(*C1, Overflow);
2551 break;
2552 case Intrinsic::ssub_with_overflow:
2553 Res = C0->ssub_ov(*C1, Overflow);
2554 break;
2555 case Intrinsic::usub_with_overflow:
2556 Res = C0->usub_ov(*C1, Overflow);
2557 break;
2558 case Intrinsic::smul_with_overflow:
2559 Res = C0->smul_ov(*C1, Overflow);
2560 break;
2561 case Intrinsic::umul_with_overflow:
2562 Res = C0->umul_ov(*C1, Overflow);
2563 break;
2564 }
2565 Constant *Ops[] = {
2566 ConstantInt::get(Ty->getContext(), Res),
2567 ConstantInt::get(Type::getInt1Ty(Ty->getContext()), Overflow)
2568 };
2569 return ConstantStruct::get(cast<StructType>(Ty), Ops);
2570 }
2571 case Intrinsic::uadd_sat:
2572 case Intrinsic::sadd_sat:
2573 if (!C0 && !C1)
2574 return UndefValue::get(Ty);
2575 if (!C0 || !C1)
2576 return Constant::getAllOnesValue(Ty);
2577 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::uadd_sat)
2578 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, C0->uadd_sat(*C1));
2579 else
2580 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, C0->sadd_sat(*C1));
2581 case Intrinsic::usub_sat:
2582 case Intrinsic::ssub_sat:
2583 if (!C0 && !C1)
2584 return UndefValue::get(Ty);
2585 if (!C0 || !C1)
2586 return Constant::getNullValue(Ty);
2587 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::usub_sat)
2588 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, C0->usub_sat(*C1));
2589 else
2590 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, C0->ssub_sat(*C1));
2591 case Intrinsic::cttz:
2592 case Intrinsic::ctlz:
2593 assert(C1 && "Must be constant int");
2594
2595 // cttz(0, 1) and ctlz(0, 1) are undef.
2596 if (C1->isOneValue() && (!C0 || C0->isNullValue()))
2597 return UndefValue::get(Ty);
2598 if (!C0)
2599 return Constant::getNullValue(Ty);
2600 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::cttz)
2601 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, C0->countTrailingZeros());
2602 else
2603 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, C0->countLeadingZeros());
2604
2605 case Intrinsic::abs:
2606 // Undef or minimum val operand with poison min --> undef
2607 assert(C1 && "Must be constant int");
2608 if (C1->isOneValue() && (!C0 || C0->isMinSignedValue()))
2609 return UndefValue::get(Ty);
2610
2611 // Undef operand with no poison min --> 0 (sign bit must be clear)
2612 if (C1->isNullValue() && !C0)
2613 return Constant::getNullValue(Ty);
2614
2615 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, C0->abs());
2616 }
2617
2618 return nullptr;
2619 }
2620
2621 // Support ConstantVector in case we have an Undef in the top.
2622 if ((isa<ConstantVector>(Operands[0]) ||
2623 isa<ConstantDataVector>(Operands[0])) &&
2624 // Check for default rounding mode.
2625 // FIXME: Support other rounding modes?
2626 isa<ConstantInt>(Operands[1]) &&
2627 cast<ConstantInt>(Operands[1])->getValue() == 4) {
2628 auto *Op = cast<Constant>(Operands[0]);
2629 switch (IntrinsicID) {
2630 default: break;
2631 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vcvtss2si32:
2632 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vcvtss2si64:
2633 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vcvtsd2si32:
2634 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vcvtsd2si64:
2635 if (ConstantFP *FPOp =
2636 dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantFP>(Op->getAggregateElement(0U)))
2637 return ConstantFoldSSEConvertToInt(FPOp->getValueAPF(),
2638 /*roundTowardZero=*/false, Ty,
2639 /*IsSigned*/true);
2640 break;
2641 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vcvtss2usi32:
2642 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vcvtss2usi64:
2643 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vcvtsd2usi32:
2644 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_vcvtsd2usi64:
2645 if (ConstantFP *FPOp =
2646 dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantFP>(Op->getAggregateElement(0U)))
2647 return ConstantFoldSSEConvertToInt(FPOp->getValueAPF(),
2648 /*roundTowardZero=*/false, Ty,
2649 /*IsSigned*/false);
2650 break;
2651 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_cvttss2si:
2652 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_cvttss2si64:
2653 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_cvttsd2si:
2654 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_cvttsd2si64:
2655 if (ConstantFP *FPOp =
2656 dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantFP>(Op->getAggregateElement(0U)))
2657 return ConstantFoldSSEConvertToInt(FPOp->getValueAPF(),
2658 /*roundTowardZero=*/true, Ty,
2659 /*IsSigned*/true);
2660 break;
2661 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_cvttss2usi:
2662 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_cvttss2usi64:
2663 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_cvttsd2usi:
2664 case Intrinsic::x86_avx512_cvttsd2usi64:
2665 if (ConstantFP *FPOp =
2666 dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantFP>(Op->getAggregateElement(0U)))
2667 return ConstantFoldSSEConvertToInt(FPOp->getValueAPF(),
2668 /*roundTowardZero=*/true, Ty,
2669 /*IsSigned*/false);
2670 break;
2671 }
2672 }
2673 return nullptr;
2674}
2675
2676static APFloat ConstantFoldAMDGCNCubeIntrinsic(Intrinsic::ID IntrinsicID,
2677 const APFloat &S0,
2678 const APFloat &S1,
2679 const APFloat &S2) {
2680 unsigned ID;
2681 const fltSemantics &Sem = S0.getSemantics();
2682 APFloat MA(Sem), SC(Sem), TC(Sem);
2683 if (abs(S2) >= abs(S0) && abs(S2) >= abs(S1)) {
2684 if (S2.isNegative() && S2.isNonZero() && !S2.isNaN()) {
2685 // S2 < 0
2686 ID = 5;
2687 SC = -S0;
2688 } else {
2689 ID = 4;
2690 SC = S0;
2691 }
2692 MA = S2;
2693 TC = -S1;
2694 } else if (abs(S1) >= abs(S0)) {
2695 if (S1.isNegative() && S1.isNonZero() && !S1.isNaN()) {
2696 // S1 < 0
2697 ID = 3;
2698 TC = -S2;
2699 } else {
2700 ID = 2;
2701 TC = S2;
2702 }
2703 MA = S1;
2704 SC = S0;
2705 } else {
2706 if (S0.isNegative() && S0.isNonZero() && !S0.isNaN()) {
2707 // S0 < 0
2708 ID = 1;
2709 SC = S2;
2710 } else {
2711 ID = 0;
2712 SC = -S2;
2713 }
2714 MA = S0;
2715 TC = -S1;
2716 }
2717 switch (IntrinsicID) {
2718 default:
2719 llvm_unreachable("unhandled amdgcn cube intrinsic");
2720 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cubeid:
2721 return APFloat(Sem, ID);
2722 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cubema:
2723 return MA + MA;
2724 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cubesc:
2725 return SC;
2726 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cubetc:
2727 return TC;
2728 }
2729}
2730
2731static Constant *ConstantFoldScalarCall3(StringRef Name,
2732 Intrinsic::ID IntrinsicID,
2733 Type *Ty,
2734 ArrayRef<Constant *> Operands,
2735 const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI,
2736 const CallBase *Call) {
2737 assert(Operands.size() == 3 && "Wrong number of operands.");
2738
2739 if (const auto *Op1 = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Operands[0])) {
2740 if (const auto *Op2 = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Operands[1])) {
2741 if (const auto *Op3 = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Operands[2])) {
2742 switch (IntrinsicID) {
2743 default: break;
2744 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_fma_legacy: {
2745 const APFloat &C1 = Op1->getValueAPF();
2746 const APFloat &C2 = Op2->getValueAPF();
2747 // The legacy behaviour is that multiplying +/- 0.0 by anything, even
2748 // NaN or infinity, gives +0.0.
2749 if (C1.isZero() || C2.isZero()) {
2750 const APFloat &C3 = Op3->getValueAPF();
2751 // It's tempting to just return C3 here, but that would give the
2752 // wrong result if C3 was -0.0.
2753 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), APFloat(0.0f) + C3);
2754 }
2755 LLVM_FALLTHROUGH;
2756 }
2757 case Intrinsic::fma:
2758 case Intrinsic::fmuladd: {
2759 APFloat V = Op1->getValueAPF();
2760 V.fusedMultiplyAdd(Op2->getValueAPF(), Op3->getValueAPF(),
2761 APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven);
2762 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), V);
2763 }
2764 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cubeid:
2765 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cubema:
2766 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cubesc:
2767 case Intrinsic::amdgcn_cubetc: {
2768 APFloat V = ConstantFoldAMDGCNCubeIntrinsic(
2769 IntrinsicID, Op1->getValueAPF(), Op2->getValueAPF(),
2770 Op3->getValueAPF());
2771 return ConstantFP::get(Ty->getContext(), V);
2772 }
2773 }
2774 }
2775 }
2776 }
2777
2778 if (const auto *Op1 = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Operands[0])) {
2779 if (const auto *Op2 = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Operands[1])) {
2780 if (const auto *Op3 = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Operands[2])) {
2781 switch (IntrinsicID) {
2782 default: break;
2783 case Intrinsic::smul_fix:
2784 case Intrinsic::smul_fix_sat: {
2785 // This code performs rounding towards negative infinity in case the
2786 // result cannot be represented exactly for the given scale. Targets
2787 // that do care about rounding should use a target hook for specifying
2788 // how rounding should be done, and provide their own folding to be
2789 // consistent with rounding. This is the same approach as used by
2790 // DAGTypeLegalizer::ExpandIntRes_MULFIX.
2791 const APInt &Lhs = Op1->getValue();
2792 const APInt &Rhs = Op2->getValue();
2793 unsigned Scale = Op3->getValue().getZExtValue();
2794 unsigned Width = Lhs.getBitWidth();
2795 assert(Scale < Width && "Illegal scale.");
2796 unsigned ExtendedWidth = Width * 2;
2797 APInt Product = (Lhs.sextOrSelf(ExtendedWidth) *
2798 Rhs.sextOrSelf(ExtendedWidth)).ashr(Scale);
2799 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::smul_fix_sat) {
2800 APInt MaxValue =
2801 APInt::getSignedMaxValue(Width).sextOrSelf(ExtendedWidth);
2802 APInt MinValue =
2803 APInt::getSignedMinValue(Width).sextOrSelf(ExtendedWidth);
2804 Product = APIntOps::smin(Product, MaxValue);
2805 Product = APIntOps::smax(Product, MinValue);
2806 }
2807 return ConstantInt::get(Ty->getContext(),
2808 Product.sextOrTrunc(Width));
2809 }
2810 }
2811 }
2812 }
2813 }
2814
2815 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::fshl || IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::fshr) {
2816 const APInt *C0, *C1, *C2;
2817 if (!getConstIntOrUndef(Operands[0], C0) ||
2818 !getConstIntOrUndef(Operands[1], C1) ||
2819 !getConstIntOrUndef(Operands[2], C2))
2820 return nullptr;
2821
2822 bool IsRight = IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::fshr;
2823 if (!C2)
2824 return Operands[IsRight ? 1 : 0];
2825 if (!C0 && !C1)
2826 return UndefValue::get(Ty);
2827
2828 // The shift amount is interpreted as modulo the bitwidth. If the shift
2829 // amount is effectively 0, avoid UB due to oversized inverse shift below.
2830 unsigned BitWidth = C2->getBitWidth();
2831 unsigned ShAmt = C2->urem(BitWidth);
2832 if (!ShAmt)
2833 return Operands[IsRight ? 1 : 0];
2834
2835 // (C0 << ShlAmt) | (C1 >> LshrAmt)
2836 unsigned LshrAmt = IsRight ? ShAmt : BitWidth - ShAmt;
2837 unsigned ShlAmt = !IsRight ? ShAmt : BitWidth - ShAmt;
2838 if (!C0)
2839 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, C1->lshr(LshrAmt));
2840 if (!C1)
2841 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, C0->shl(ShlAmt));
2842 return ConstantInt::get(Ty, C0->shl(ShlAmt) | C1->lshr(LshrAmt));
2843 }
2844
2845 return nullptr;
2846}
2847
2848static Constant *ConstantFoldScalarCall(StringRef Name,
2849 Intrinsic::ID IntrinsicID,
2850 Type *Ty,
2851 ArrayRef<Constant *> Operands,
2852 const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI,
2853 const CallBase *Call) {
2854 if (Operands.size() == 1)
2855 return ConstantFoldScalarCall1(Name, IntrinsicID, Ty, Operands, TLI, Call);
2856
2857 if (Operands.size() == 2)
2858 return ConstantFoldScalarCall2(Name, IntrinsicID, Ty, Operands, TLI, Call);
2859
2860 if (Operands.size() == 3)
2861 return ConstantFoldScalarCall3(Name, IntrinsicID, Ty, Operands, TLI, Call);
2862
2863 return nullptr;
2864}
2865
2866static Constant *ConstantFoldVectorCall(StringRef Name,
2867 Intrinsic::ID IntrinsicID,
2868 VectorType *VTy,
2869 ArrayRef<Constant *> Operands,
2870 const DataLayout &DL,
2871 const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI,
2872 const CallBase *Call) {
2873 // Do not iterate on scalable vector. The number of elements is unknown at
2874 // compile-time.
2875 if (isa<ScalableVectorType>(VTy))
2876 return nullptr;
2877
2878 auto *FVTy = cast<FixedVectorType>(VTy);
2879
2880 SmallVector<Constant *, 4> Result(FVTy->getNumElements());
2881 SmallVector<Constant *, 4> Lane(Operands.size());
2882 Type *Ty = FVTy->getElementType();
2883
2884 switch (IntrinsicID) {
2885 case Intrinsic::masked_load: {
2886 auto *SrcPtr = Operands[0];
2887 auto *Mask = Operands[2];
2888 auto *Passthru = Operands[3];
2889
2890 Constant *VecData = ConstantFoldLoadFromConstPtr(SrcPtr, FVTy, DL);
2891
2892 SmallVector<Constant *, 32> NewElements;
2893 for (unsigned I = 0, E = FVTy->getNumElements(); I != E; ++I) {
2894 auto *MaskElt = Mask->getAggregateElement(I);
2895 if (!MaskElt)
2896 break;
2897 auto *PassthruElt = Passthru->getAggregateElement(I);
2898 auto *VecElt = VecData ? VecData->getAggregateElement(I) : nullptr;
2899 if (isa<UndefValue>(MaskElt)) {
2900 if (PassthruElt)
2901 NewElements.push_back(PassthruElt);
2902 else if (VecElt)
2903 NewElements.push_back(VecElt);
2904 else
2905 return nullptr;
2906 }
2907 if (MaskElt->isNullValue()) {
2908 if (!PassthruElt)
2909 return nullptr;
2910 NewElements.push_back(PassthruElt);
2911 } else if (MaskElt->isOneValue()) {
2912 if (!VecElt)
2913 return nullptr;
2914 NewElements.push_back(VecElt);
2915 } else {
2916 return nullptr;
2917 }
2918 }
2919 if (NewElements.size() != FVTy->getNumElements())
2920 return nullptr;
2921 return ConstantVector::get(NewElements);
2922 }
2923 case Intrinsic::arm_mve_vctp8:
2924 case Intrinsic::arm_mve_vctp16:
2925 case Intrinsic::arm_mve_vctp32:
2926 case Intrinsic::arm_mve_vctp64: {
2927 if (auto *Op = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Operands[0])) {
2928 unsigned Lanes = FVTy->getNumElements();
2929 uint64_t Limit = Op->getZExtValue();
2930 // vctp64 are currently modelled as returning a v4i1, not a v2i1. Make
2931 // sure we get the limit right in that case and set all relevant lanes.
2932 if (IntrinsicID == Intrinsic::arm_mve_vctp64)
2933 Limit *= 2;
2934
2935 SmallVector<Constant *, 16> NCs;
2936 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Lanes; i++) {
2937 if (i < Limit)
2938 NCs.push_back(ConstantInt::getTrue(Ty));
2939 else
2940 NCs.push_back(ConstantInt::getFalse(Ty));
2941 }
2942 return ConstantVector::get(NCs);
2943 }
2944 break;
2945 }
2946 case Intrinsic::get_active_lane_mask: {
2947 auto *Op0 = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Operands[0]);
2948 auto *Op1 = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(Operands[1]);
2949 if (Op0 && Op1) {
2950 unsigned Lanes = FVTy->getNumElements();
2951 uint64_t Base = Op0->getZExtValue();
2952 uint64_t Limit = Op1->getZExtValue();
2953
2954 SmallVector<Constant *, 16> NCs;
2955 for (unsigned i = 0; i < Lanes; i++) {
2956 if (Base + i < Limit)
2957 NCs.push_back(ConstantInt::getTrue(Ty));
2958 else
2959 NCs.push_back(ConstantInt::getFalse(Ty));
2960 }
2961 return ConstantVector::get(NCs);
2962 }
2963 break;
2964 }
2965 default:
2966 break;
2967 }
2968
2969 for (unsigned I = 0, E = FVTy->getNumElements(); I != E; ++I) {
2970 // Gather a column of constants.
2971 for (unsigned J = 0, JE = Operands.size(); J != JE; ++J) {
2972 // Some intrinsics use a scalar type for certain arguments.
2973 if (hasVectorInstrinsicScalarOpd(IntrinsicID, J)) {
2974 Lane[J] = Operands[J];
2975 continue;
2976 }
2977
2978 Constant *Agg = Operands[J]->getAggregateElement(I);
2979 if (!Agg)
2980 return nullptr;
2981
2982 Lane[J] = Agg;
2983 }
2984
2985 // Use the regular scalar folding to simplify this column.
2986 Constant *Folded =
2987 ConstantFoldScalarCall(Name, IntrinsicID, Ty, Lane, TLI, Call);
2988 if (!Folded)
2989 return nullptr;
2990 Result[I] = Folded;
2991 }
2992
2993 return ConstantVector::get(Result);
2994}
2995
2996} // end anonymous namespace
2997
2998Constant *llvm::ConstantFoldCall(const CallBase *Call, Function *F,
2999 ArrayRef<Constant *> Operands,
3000 const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI) {
3001 if (Call->isNoBuiltin())
3002 return nullptr;
3003 if (!F->hasName())
3004 return nullptr;
3005 StringRef Name = F->getName();
3006
3007 Type *Ty = F->getReturnType();
3008
3009 if (auto *VTy = dyn_cast<VectorType>(Ty))
3010 return ConstantFoldVectorCall(Name, F->getIntrinsicID(), VTy, Operands,
3011 F->getParent()->getDataLayout(), TLI, Call);
3012
3013 return ConstantFoldScalarCall(Name, F->getIntrinsicID(), Ty, Operands, TLI,
3014 Call);
3015}
3016
3017bool llvm::isMathLibCallNoop(const CallBase *Call,
3018 const TargetLibraryInfo *TLI) {
3019 // FIXME: Refactor this code; this duplicates logic in LibCallsShrinkWrap
3020 // (and to some extent ConstantFoldScalarCall).
3021 if (Call->isNoBuiltin() || Call->isStrictFP())
3022 return false;
3023 Function *F = Call->getCalledFunction();
3024 if (!F)
3025 return false;
3026
3027 LibFunc Func;
3028 if (!TLI || !TLI->getLibFunc(*F, Func))
3029 return false;
3030
3031 if (Call->getNumArgOperands() == 1) {
3032 if (ConstantFP *OpC = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Call->getArgOperand(0))) {
3033 const APFloat &Op = OpC->getValueAPF();
3034 switch (Func) {
3035 case LibFunc_logl:
3036 case LibFunc_log:
3037 case LibFunc_logf:
3038 case LibFunc_log2l:
3039 case LibFunc_log2:
3040 case LibFunc_log2f:
3041 case LibFunc_log10l:
3042 case LibFunc_log10:
3043 case LibFunc_log10f:
3044 return Op.isNaN() || (!Op.isZero() && !Op.isNegative());
3045
3046 case LibFunc_expl:
3047 case LibFunc_exp:
3048 case LibFunc_expf:
3049 // FIXME: These boundaries are slightly conservative.
3050 if (OpC->getType()->isDoubleTy())
3051 return !(Op < APFloat(-745.0) || Op > APFloat(709.0));
3052 if (OpC->getType()->isFloatTy())
3053 return !(Op < APFloat(-103.0f) || Op > APFloat(88.0f));
3054 break;
3055
3056 case LibFunc_exp2l:
3057 case LibFunc_exp2:
3058 case LibFunc_exp2f:

3060 if (OpC->getType()->isDoubleTy())
3061 return !(Op < APFloat(-1074.0) || Op > APFloat(1023.0));
3062 if (OpC->getType()->isFloatTy())
3063 return !(Op < APFloat(-149.0f) || Op > APFloat(127.0f));

3066 case LibFunc_sinl:
3067 case LibFunc_sin:
3068 case LibFunc_sinf:
3069 case LibFunc_cosl:
3070 case LibFunc_cos:
3071 case LibFunc_cosf:
3072 return !Op.isInfinity();

3074 case LibFunc_tanl:
3075 case LibFunc_tan:
3076 case LibFunc_tanf: {

3078 // FIXME: The computation isn't done in the right precision.
3079 Type *Ty = OpC->getType();
3080 if (Ty->isDoubleTy() || Ty->isFloatTy() || Ty->isHalfTy()) {

3087 case LibFunc_asinl:
3088 case LibFunc_asin:
3089 case LibFunc_asinf:
3090 case LibFunc_acosl:
3091 case LibFunc_acos:
3092 case LibFunc_acosf:

3094 Op > APFloat(Op.getSemantics(), "1"));

3098 case LibFunc_sinhf:
3099 case LibFunc_coshf:

3101 case LibFunc_coshl:
3102 // FIXME: These boundaries are slightly conservative.
3103 if (OpC->getType()->isDoubleTy())
3104 return !(Op < APFloat(-710.0) || Op > APFloat(710.0));
3105 if (OpC->getType()->isFloatTy())
3106 return !(Op < APFloat(-89.0f) || Op > APFloat(89.0f));

3109 case LibFunc_sqrtl:
3110 case LibFunc_sqrt:
3111 case LibFunc_sqrtf:
3112 return Op.isNaN() || Op.isZero() || !Op.isNegative();

3115 // maybe others?
3116 default:
3117 break;

3119 }
3120 }
3121
3122 if (Call->getNumArgOperands() == 2) {
3123 ConstantFP *Op0C = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Call->getArgOperand(0));
3124 ConstantFP *Op1C = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(Call->getArgOperand(1));
3125 if (Op0C && Op1C) {
3126 const APFloat &Op0 = Op0C->getValueAPF();
3127 const APFloat &Op1 = Op1C->getValueAPF();
3128
3129 switch (Func) {
3130 case LibFunc_powl:
3131 case LibFunc_pow:
3132 case LibFunc_powf: {
3133 // FIXME: Stop using the host math library.
3134 // FIXME: The computation isn't done in the right precision.
3135 Type *Ty = Op0C->getType();
3136 if (Ty->isDoubleTy() || Ty->isFloatTy() || Ty->isHalfTy()) {
3137 if (Ty == Op1C->getType()) {
3138 double Op0V = getValueAsDouble(Op0C);
3139 double Op1V = getValueAsDouble(Op1C);
3140 return ConstantFoldBinaryFP(pow, Op0V, Op1V, Ty) != nullptr;
3141 }
3142 }
3143 break;
3144 }
3145
3146 case LibFunc_fmodl:
3147 case LibFunc_fmod:
3148 case LibFunc_fmodf:
3149 case LibFunc_remainderl:
3150 case LibFunc_remainder:
3151 case LibFunc_remainderf:
3152 return Op0.isNaN() || Op1.isNaN() ||
3153 (!Op0.isInfinity() && !Op1.isZero());
3154
3155 default:
3156 break;
3157 }
3158 }
3159 }

3161 return false;
